Class LegacyDatasetResource

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gbif.registry.ws.resources.legacy.LegacyDatasetResource

  • public class LegacyDatasetResource
extends Object
    Handle all legacy web service Dataset requests (excluding IPT requests), previously handled by the GBRDS.

      • registerDataset

        public javax.ws.rs.core.Response registerDataset(@InjectParam
                                                 LegacyDataset dataset,
                                                 @Context
                                                 javax.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext security)
        Register GBRDS dataset, handling incoming request with path /resource. The primary contact, publishing organization key, and resource name are mandatory. Only after both the dataset and primary contact have been persisted is a Response with Status.CREATED (201) returned.
        Parameters:
        dataset - IptDataset with HTTP form parameters having been injected from Jersey
        security - SecurityContext (security related information)
        Returns:
        Response
        See Also:
        IptResource.registerDataset(org.gbif.registry.ws.model.LegacyDataset, javax.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext)

      • updateDataset

        public javax.ws.rs.core.Response updateDataset(UUID datasetKey,
                                               @InjectParam
                                               LegacyDataset dataset,
                                               @Context
                                               javax.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext security)
        Update GBRDS Dataset, handling incoming request with path /resource/{key}. The publishing organization key is mandatory (supplied in the credentials not the parameters). The primary contact is not required, but if any of the primary contact parameters were included in the request, it is required. This is the difference between this method and registerDataset. Only after both the dataset and optional primary contact have been updated is a Response with Status.OK (201) returned.
        Parameters:
        datasetKey - dataset key (UUID) coming in as path param
        dataset - IptDataset with HTTP form parameters having been injected from Jersey
        security - SecurityContext (security related information)
        Returns:
        Response with Status.CREATED (201) if successful

      • datasetsForOrganization

        public javax.ws.rs.core.Response datasetsForOrganization(UUID organizationKey)
        Retrieve all Datasets owned by an organization, handling incoming request with path /resource. The publishing organization query parameter is mandatory. Only after both the organizationKey is verified to correspond to an existing organization, is a Response including the list of Datasets returned.
        Parameters:
        organizationKey - organization key (UUID) coming in as query param
        Returns:
        Response with list of Datasets or empty list with error message if none found

      • readDataset

        public javax.ws.rs.core.Response readDataset(UUID datasetKey)
        Read GBRDS Dataset, handling incoming request with path /resource/{key}.
        Parameters:
        datasetKey - dataset key (UUID) coming in as path param
        Returns:
        Response with Status.OK (200) if dataset exists

      • deleteDataset

        public javax.ws.rs.core.Response deleteDataset(UUID datasetKey)
        Delete GBRDS Dataset, handling incoming request with path /resource/{key}. Only credentials are mandatory. If deletion is successful, returns Response with Status.OK.
        Parameters:
        datasetKey - dataset key (UUID) coming in as path param
        Returns:
        Response with Status.OK if successful
        See Also:
        IptResource.deleteDataset(java.util.UUID)
